mea $n the sea-elves, sent me out of our city, on an expedition to expand
mea $n the length of our rule. It took many days of climb around, inside
mea $n caves, day after day i travled, with out the sun, or any light
mea $n except that of my torch, tell finally i stepped out of the caves
mea $n and onto the beach below, what i saw is a sight that i shall never
mea $n forget, the lake that you now stand above is the most beutifall thing
mea $n i have ever seen. I stayed here for many years, building all that
mea $n you can see on the lake, news of my stay attracked many a people
mea $n including my good friend, zion, a human, who has help me to build
mea $n much, including the device. After about ten years, the lake was
mea $n hit with a devistating earthquake, that not only closed off the
mea $n only way back to my people, but opened up a taribal place. On
mea $n north east end of the lake a large den opened which is infested with
mea $n a large monster, and her progen, which i have named Learra. soon
mea $n enough, i shall go to fight her, and we shall see who comes up the
mea $n victor."
endif
