On Clemancy Lake~
To the northeasterly directions you can see the seemingly endless expanse 
that is the lake.  It shimmers softly as you look at its serene surface.  To 
the North you can see a small isle beyond the immediate waters.  As you 
look south you can see a wall of reeds that goes for a ways to the east and 
to the west.  To the southeast you can see a break in the wall.  To the east 
and  west the shoreline continues somewhat parallel to the wall of reeds.
